featured_reviews.review_id: Masjid Khairuddin is at Hall Bazar. It is famously known as Jama Masjid, is a beautiful Mosque built by Muhammad Khairuddin in 1876 CE. It is one of the most admired religious centres for locals as well as tourists. It is renowned for its beautiful architectural design. Holds a great importance in India's freedom struggle.

featured_reviews.review_id: Really nice masjid with a traditional islamic design and architecture, located just 1.5 kms away form Amritsar railway station. I stayed here for a half day, masjid has some plants and neem tree on the compound creating a really peaceful ambiance in midst of chaotic city, here people giving more importance for greenery as the way prophet taught us. Students stay in this masjid for studying quran and islamic studies, also they take care of the masjid compund by cleaning and maintaining the building.
